docs AllPosts
    Returns all blog posts as a list of BlogPost dicts.
done

func AllPosts
    emit result as list
    fail error as text
body
    p1 = {slug: "hello-world", title: "Hello World", content: "Welcome to our first blog post! This is a simple example of a forai-powered blog."}
    p2 = {slug: "forai-intro", title: "Introduction to forai", content: "forai is a pipeline-based language where sources produce events, funcs compute, and flows wire everything together."}
    posts = [p1, p2]
    emit posts
done

test AllPosts
    all = AllPosts()
    ok = true
    must ok == true
done
